\pard\plain\tx9821\plain\f0\fs20\cf0\par
\tx9821\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart AdenomysisAPMeasure}The features were more apparent in the {\field{\*\fldinst{MERGEFIELD LargerMyometrium}}{\*\wpfldparam{LargerMyometrium}}{\fldrslt{LargerMyometrium}}} myometrium, which was relatively enlarged (AP diameter of the anterior and posterior myometrium measured {\field{\*\fldinst{MERGEFIELD AnteriorAPMeasure}}{\*\wpfldparam{AnteriorAPMeasure}}{\fldrslt{AnteriorAPMeasure}}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{MERGEFIELD PosteriorAPMeasure}}{\*\wpfldparam{PosteriorAPMeasure}}{\fldrslt{PosteriorAPMeasure}}}mm respectively). {\*\bkmkend AdenomysisAPMeasure}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa0\tx9821\ql\vertalt\par
\pard\plain\tx9821\plain\f0\fs20\cf0\par
\tx9821\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart EMInterfaceLoss}A loss of interface between the endometrium and myometrium was also apparent, a key feature of adenomyosis. {\*\bkmkend EMInterfaceLoss}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa0\tx9821\ql\vertalt\par
