\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart SalineProc1}An uncomplicated transcervical saline instillation of the uterine cavity was performed.  A 14G plastic feeding tube was guided into the uterine cavity.  20 ml of Normal saline was injected and good cavity distension was achieved. This revealed a normal endometrial cavity.{\*\bkmkend SalineProc1}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart SalineProc2}An uncomplicated transcervical saline instillation of the uterine cavity was performed.  A 14G plastic feeding tube was guided into the uterine cavity.  20 ml of Normal saline was injected and good cavity distension was achieved. This revealed an endometrial polyp.{\*\bkmkend SalineProc2}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart SalineProc4}An uncomplicated transcervical saline instillation of the uterine cavity was performed.  A 14G plastic feeding tube was guided into the uterine cavity.  20 ml of Normal saline was injected and good cavity distension was achieved. This revealed two endometrial polyps.{\*\bkmkend SalineProc4}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart SalineProc3}An uncomplicated transcervical saline instillation of the uterine cavity was performed.  A 14G plastic feeding tube was guided into the uterine cavity.  20 ml of Normal saline was injected and good cavity distension was achieved. This revealed a submucosal fibroid.{\*\bkmkend SalineProc3}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Agitated1}An uncomplicated tubal patency study was performed using agitated saline.  Free flow of agitated saline was identified along both fallopian tubes and into the pelvis, confirming bilateral tubal patency.{\*\bkmkend Agitated1}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Agitated2}An uncomplicated tubal patency study was performed using agitated saline contrast material.   Free flow of contrast medium was demonstrated along the right fallopian tube and into the pelvis.  The left tube showed no filling beyond the cornu.  This is suggestive of unilateral tubal blockage, although tubal spasm cannot be excluded.{\*\bkmkend Agitated2}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Agitated3}An uncomplicated tubal patency study was performed using agitated saline material.   Free flow of contrast medium was demonstrated along the left fallopian tube, and into the pelvis.  The right tube showed no filling beyond the cornu.  This is suggestive of unilateral tubal blockage, although tubal spasm cannot be excluded.{\*\bkmkend Agitated3}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Agitated5}An uncomplicated tubal patency study was performed using agitated saline.  No free fill and spill of saline was identified along either fallopian tube, suggestive of bilateral tubal spasm or blockage.{\*\bkmkend Agitated5}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Agitated4}Assessment of fallopian tube patency could not be performed because of unsuccessful cannulation of the cervical canal.{\*\bkmkend Agitated4}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Levovist1}An uncomplicated tubal patency study was performed using sonographic contrast material.  Free flow of contrast medium was identified along both fallopian tubes and into the pelvis, confirming bilateral tubal patency.{\*\bkmkend Levovist1}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Levovist2}An uncomplicated tubal patency study was performed using agitated saline contrast material.   Free flow of contrast medium was demonstrated along the right fallopian tube and into the pelvis.  The left tube showed no filling beyond the cornu.  This is suggestive of unilateral tubal blockage, although tubal spasm cannot be excluded.{\*\bkmkend Levovist2}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt\par
\plain\f0\fs20\cf0{\*\bkmkstart Levovist3}An uncomplicated tubal patency study was performed using sonographic contrast material.   Free flow of contrast medium was demonstrated along the left fallopian tube, and into the pelvis.  The right tube showed no filling beyond the cornu.  This is suggestive of unilateral tubal blockage, although tubal spasm cannot be excluded{\*\bkmkend Levovist3}\li0\fi0\ri0\sb0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ql\vertalt .\par
